<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-23T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-23T03:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12273: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-23T16:00:00+08:00">January 23, 1933—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 23—5:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>78. Young Marshal left Peiping yesterday at 2 p.m., arrived Nanking 7
                            p.m. Unconfirmed rumors here connect his visit to Nanking with presence
                            there of Tuan Chi-jui. See also Legation’s 71, January 22, 3 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>